OL,3,C'You go in a boy and come out a man':
OL,4,CVeteran shares D-Day journey
OL,6,FHe said: "You go in as a boy, but you
OL,7,Fcome out a man. It did shape your
OL,8,Flife. I've seen things I never thought
OL,9,FI'd see in my lifetime."
OL,11,FOne of the most harrowing sights came
OL,12,Fin April 1945, when he entered the
OL,13,FBergen-Belsen concentration camp.
OL,15,FHe said: "It was a horrible sight, and
OL,16,Fthe smell...I said to my co-driver at
OL,17,Fthe time, I said 'where's God to allow
OL,18,Fall this death and destruction?'"
