OL,3,C'You go in a boy and come out a man':
OL,4,CVeteran shares D-Day journey
OL,6,FDuring the Second World War, it is
OL,7,Festimated that at least 70,000 people
OL,8,Fwere killed at the Bergen-Belsen Camp.
OL,10,FRichard said: "There was death and
OL,11,Fdying and all the inmates were
OL,12,Fcowering if you went near them."
OL,14,FTen months earlier, the D-Day landings
OL,15,Fsaw 156,000 Allied troops arrive for a
OL,16,Fcombined naval, air and land assault
OL,17,Fon Nazi-occupied France.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
