OL,3,C'You go in a boy and come out a man':
OL,4,CVeteran shares D-Day journey
OL,6,FRichard and his battalion advanced
OL,7,Fthrough France, before entering
OL,8,FBelgium, Holland, and eventually
OL,9,FGermany.
OL,11,FAs the invasion of Normandy is
OL,12,Fcommemorated on its 80th anniversary,
OL,13,FRichard believes he is the only member
OL,14,Fof his battalion still alive.
OL,16,FHe said: "I don't think you're proud,
OL,17,Fyou're just sad for your pals that
OL,18,Fyou've missed. All your mates were
OL,19,Fgetting knocked off. I think I'm the
OL,20,Flast one.
